Job Description:
COMPANY OVERVIEW

Domo puts data to work to help everyone multiply their impact. Domo gives every kind of user real-time insights they can act on, with secure, easy-to-use, AI-powered data experience that drive a culture of data curiosity.

POSITION SUMMARY

Our software engineering team is looking for an experienced AI/ML engineer to be part of a fast-paced, high-energy team. Our engineers are serious about the success of the company and are given the tools and environment they need to succeed. If you are an experienced engineer with a passion for technology and solving complex business problems using AI/ML and believe planning, hard work, teamwork, and quality is what it takes to succeed, then this is the job for you.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

Work with customers, technical architects, and data scientists to define the architecture and requirements for micro-services that power an end-to-end ML pipeline, including model training, hosting and monitoring;
Lead the design and development of AI/ML products to fulfill customer needs;
Develop strategies with other engineering teams to optimize and scale business application delivery;
Develop methods and tools to monitor the performance and reliability of customer business applications.

JOB REQUIREMENTS

5+ years of software development experience in Python and/or Java;
Bachelor's degree or higher in Computer Science, Data Science or a related field;
Knowledge of and experience deploying models and monitoring model performance;
Demonstrated aptitude for learning new technologies;
Ability to communicate and interface with technical and non-technical members of the organization.

NICE TO HAVE

Experience with tools and methodologies used to create end-to-end AI-powered applications, including embedding models, vector databases, LLMs, prompt engineering, fine-tuning, etc.;
Experience working with Jupyter, AWS Sagemaker or similar tools;
Understanding of metrics for evaluating model performance;
Experience using various database technologies such as MySQL, Oracle, MS SQL, etc.;
Experience with RESTful API patterns and practices.

LOCATION: American Fork, UT

Domo is an equal opportunity employer.

